horse paddock
Homonym Number:
Word Class: noun
Sense Number:
Definition:a paddock in which pack, draught, or saddle horses are grazed when not working [adjacent to a homestead, outstation or shepherds' quarters].


Origin: [none]
Register:
Register 2:
Flag: Farm Words
Domain: Rural
Region: [none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: also horse-paddock
